{"key":"post-10933799","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10933799</id>\n<content>Actually, if you clone for the qualities you want, you have a good chance of getting them.&amp;nbsp; Even better is to isolate a pure single sector strain on agar, and then the variance between mushrooms will be very little.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With multispore inoculation, not all strains that emerge are compatible, so often you get several strains fruiting from various parts of the substrate, each with their own characteristics.&amp;nbsp; If you isolate a single sector strain and keep it in the refrigerator on master culture slants, you can grow the same strain from now on.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10933853</next>\n<prev>10933467</prev>\n<first>10930462</first>\n<last>10940196</last>\n<when>1251223219</when>\n<utime>08/25/09 09:00 PM</utime>\n</post>"}